<!doctype html>
<html lang='en'>
  <head>
    <meta charset='UTF-8' />
    <meta name='viewport' content='width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0' />
    <title>SAPUI5 Explorer - Privacy Policy</title>
    <style>
      * {
        box-sizing: border-box;
        margin: 0;
        padding: 0;
      }
      body {
        font-family:
          'Segoe UI',
          -apple-system,
          sans-serif;
        color: #333;
        background: #f8f9fa;
        line-height: 1.7;
      }
      .container {
        max-width: 720px;
        margin: 0 auto;
        padding: 40px 24px;
      }
      h1 {
        font-size: 28px;
        color: #0070f2;
        margin-bottom: 6px;
      }
      .subtitle {
        color: #666;
        font-size: 14px;
        margin-bottom: 32px;
      }
      h2 {
        font-size: 18px;
        color: #222;
        margin-top: 28px;
        margin-bottom: 10px;
        padding-bottom: 6px;
        border-bottom: 1px solid #e0e0e0;
      }
      p,
      li {
        font-size: 15px;
        margin-bottom: 10px;
      }
      ul {
        padding-left: 24px;
        margin-bottom: 14px;
      }
      li {
        margin-bottom: 6px;
      }
      strong {
        color: #222;
      }
      .highlight {
        background: #e8f4fd;
        border-left: 3px solid #0070f2;
        padding: 12px 16px;
        border-radius: 4px;
        margin: 16px 0;
        font-size: 14px;
      }
      .footer {
        margin-top: 40px;
        padding-top: 20px;
        border-top: 1px solid #e0e0e0;
        font-size: 13px;
        color: #888;
      }
      a {
        color: #0070f2;
        text-decoration: none;
      }
      a:hover {
        text-decoration: underline;
      }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <div class='container'>
      <h1>SAPUI5 Explorer</h1>
      <p class='subtitle'>Privacy Policy &mdash; Last updated: March 2026</p>

      <div class='highlight'>
        <strong>Summary:</strong> SAPUI5 Explorer does not collect, store, transmit
        or share any user data. All analysis is performed locally in your browser
        and never leaves your device.
      </div>

      <h2>1. What This Extension Does</h2>
      <p>
        SAPUI5 Explorer is a developer tool that analyzes SAPUI5/OpenUI5 web
        applications running in your browser. When you click the <strong
          >Analyze</strong
        > button, it inspects the active tab to extract technical information about
        the UI5 framework, components, models, views, bindings, and runtime configuration.
      </p>

      <h2>2. Data Collection</h2>
      <p>
        This extension does <strong>not</strong> collect any data. Specifically:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>No personal information is collected</li>
        <li>No browsing history is recorded</li>
        <li>No cookies are read or written</li>
        <li>No analytics or tracking scripts are included</li>
        <li>No data is transmitted to any server, third party or otherwise</li>
        <li>No user accounts or authentication are required</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>3. Data Processing</h2>
      <p>
        All processing happens <strong>entirely within your browser</strong>:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          A script is injected into the active tab only when you explicitly
          click Analyze
        </li>
        <li>
          The script reads UI5 framework objects available in the page's
          JavaScript context
        </li>
        <li>
          Results are displayed in the extension popup and held in memory only
          for the current session
        </li>
        <li>When you close the popup, the data is discarded</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>4. Data Storage</h2>
      <p>
        This extension does not use any persistent storage mechanism. No data is
        saved to local storage, session storage, IndexedDB, Chrome storage APIs
        or the filesystem. Analysis results exist only in the popup's runtime
        memory and are lost when the popup closes.
      </p>

      <h2>5. Data Sharing</h2>
      <p>
        No data is shared with anyone. The extension has no network
        functionality and makes no outbound HTTP requests. The optional <strong
          >Copy JSON</strong
        > feature copies analysis results to your local clipboard under your control.
      </p>

      <h2>6. Permissions</h2>
      <p>
        The extension requires the following permissions, used solely for its
        core functionality:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>activeTab</strong> &mdash; to access the tab you are currently viewing
          when you click the extension icon
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>scripting</strong> &mdash; to inject the analysis script into the
          page's JavaScript context
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>host_permissions (&lt;all_urls&gt;)</strong> &mdash; because SAP
          applications run on arbitrary customer domains that cannot be predefined.
          The extension only activates on explicit user action.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2>7. Third-Party Services</h2>
      <p>
        This extension does not integrate with, communicate with, or send data
        to any third-party service, API, or server.
      </p>

      <h2>8. Children's Privacy</h2>
      <p>
        This extension is a developer tool not directed at children. It does not
        knowingly collect any information from anyone, including children under
        13.
      </p>

      <h2>9. Changes to This Policy</h2>
      <p>
        If this privacy policy is updated, the changes will be reflected on this
        page with an updated revision date. Since the extension collects no
        data, significant changes are unlikely.
      </p>

      <h2>10. Contact</h2>
      <p>
        For questions about this privacy policy or the extension, please open an
        issue on the <a
          href='https://github.com/user/sapui5-explorer-extension'
          target='_blank'
          rel='noopener'>GitHub repository</a
        >.
      </p>

      <div class='footer'>
        SAPUI5 Explorer &mdash; A browser developer tool for SAPUI5/OpenUI5
        applications.
      </div>
    </div>
  </body>
</html>
